This funky classic is famous as the opening theme to the TV drama "Journey to the West."
Listening to the original again, it's hard to believe it's from almost 50 years ago - it's so cool!
I tried to give it a mix-rock feel in the style of Red Hot Chili Peppers or Rage Against the Machine.
The beginning incorporates the vocals of a Chinese folk song, and from the middle to the end I added a monkey sound effect to the guitar.
My mix-rock tracks have always been sung by singers with solid voices, but this time the original song has a stronger funk element, so I used a husky vocalist with a cool, delinquent-like voice that was included in my audio set.
